Engineer I - Process

Matrix PDM Engineering

- Pittsburgh, PA

Essential Functions
Actively supports the Company’s commitment to safety and its “Core Values.”
Represents the Company at all times with high moral standards while adhering to the Company’s “Code of Business Conduct and Ethics.”
Acquires knowledge and develops skills with all functions and deliverables in the Process Department.
Applies prescribed techniques and procedures in accordance with established criteria to perform assigned tasks.
Develops process parameters including mass flow, heat transfer, material balance capacities and rates.
Develops the system design including PFD, PID, Layouts and Specifications as instructed.
Interacts with Design/Drafting in order to produce drawings necessary for the completion of the project.
Performs computations or analysis necessary for deliverables such as line sizing, equipment specification, hydraulic analysis, expected inventories, etc.
Participates in Model Reviews, Process Hazard Analysis (PHA) sessions and HAZOP studies.
Produces necessary documentation and deliverables such as line lists, bid tabs, manuals, reports, etc. as instructed.
Observes construction activities.
Performs P&ID walk-downs.
Assists with plant start-ups as required by project.
Performs other related duties, as directed.

Qualifications
BS or MS degree in Mechanical or Chemical Engineering.
Entry-level Engineer, no experience required.
Basic knowledge of analysis tools such as HYSYS, ProMax or other simulation software.
Basic understanding of systems and mechanical and/or chemical engineering processes preferred.
Proficiency in Microsoft Office is required.
Cooperates with other team members; interacts with individuals at all organizational levels in a professional manner.
Exhibits excellent communication skills.
Demonstrates good organizational skills and ability to follow directions.

n/a

